title: For Sale:  1928A1 Thompson MG Post Sample Full Auto Tommy gun 1928 Machine Gun WWII NFA Auto Ordnance Savage
postcontent: This is a Post Sample 1928A1 Thompson Machinegun, manufactured with an original WWII parts set and a brand new Philadelphia Ordnance receiver.You must have a FFL/SOT and be able to get a LE Demonstration Letter to be able to purchase this gun. If you are unsure of the procedure, The parts set are one of the like new WWII kits from Russia. The Pistol grip numbers match the receiver; it come with a 30 round magazine, the bore on the gun is bright and clean with excellent grooves and lands. Most parts are excellent to like new condition with the exception of the wood; as the pictures show, there are some moderate scratches from use on the right and left sides of stock although the fore grip and pistol are in good condition with only moderate wear. The Soviet Union had received M3 tanks through Lend-Lease during WWII and each tank included Thompsons as standard equipment. The Thompsons were removed from the tanks and replaced with the standard Russian sub-guns for the war. The Thompsons remained in storage for 60 years before coming back to the US as parts sets. This gun has been professionally assembled and test fired. Once again it is manufactured using original WWII parts. The recoil spring and magazine spring have been replaced with brand new “Wolf” springs to give you years of trouble free operation.

Originally produced and issued to the Kaiser's army in the First World War, the rifle was retained by the German government, likely in violation of the Treaty of Versailles, to be reworked to K98k standards at Mauser Oberndorf, presumably in 1935.
